{
  "message": "fix(conformance): correct dtype fixture u8 -> uint8 naming (franken_numpy-drk4)\n\nIn NumPy's byte-width naming convention, \"u8\" means uint64 (8 bytes),\nnot uint8. The lossless_cast_destination test was using \"u8\" intending\nto test uint8 behavior, causing can_cast_lossless(u64, u32) to fail.\n\nFix: Change \"u8\" to \"uint8\" to correctly test uint8 -> u32 promotion.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
